[commands]
check_yum_update=$USER1$/check_yum_update

[name]
check_yum_update

[info]
Checks for availabla updates using the command 'yum check-updates'.

[why]
To make sure you do not miss any updates on your RedHat/CentOS linux system that uses yum as a package manager.

[how]
The plugin uses the yum command to get the number of new package available for installation.

